 the .class file under src/test/java feels tricky since javac might ignore it, and Gradle may not copy class output as expected. Another thought is generating a .java file with an embedded Base64 custom classloader at runtime, but dynamic loading isn't supported in native setups. I could use a helper bytecode to invoke a direct class method, which might work!\n\n**Clarifying reflection issues**\n\nI need to address the NoClassDefFoundError caused by a missing class. It seems like this error is arising in the reflection test. I want to ensure to provide a final and concise explanation so it's clear what’s happening. It's important to get this sorted out to avoid confusion for anyone dealing with similar issues. Let me double-check everything and make sure I accurately explain the problem and its solution.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0150a8881465fe3f016a00def099d88195840baff872778478\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAN8gJD_4mFP-DXB-AE5AUQ1CH0HXdmP6FcDqt-eQZ5vKpNr-ojhxn3Xp_Khf4-2TdqLq3K4HSYMIFS2kqZj2QwHancXXJO5YBhGDEi0N00ilZXKSsCwkVY-AJUrEDDx2nmB24ppapMeO4met9BY2SpdZd3AWWtuyMsg1YwmxxtDpV-VIG8sQWvqztsvYnkzVfzmdpkiIcI3sWg9bgOBb0r0OAz_Uj_5NMW-WvRFqyzZAJhb5ny09kS83iJZXVg4BcoiS32b4V3pHdWPWts2vkFZoOBSpEwF3ml4Wqnle5euI4hmnZ2X3CdJBeUFuDKJadnNJ9VlotlbHmCKUdWOIjwv5oYBsbYI0huV1dCCxpfbDPu6FY0TnchTSJAkDzf2TSOiIzLAmqSiVse6yrBy1_ACzXwFM3dN0eBsntNDRPjwU2vQII8q0k76Ce8ApOZnPMl51tYHxSGw9SVynlxxjQn2QgcwYaCK2dK7hsAXLUjYWwny-a62Ao_59Szxaotq9rtvtkt-z2NVEMCBBMQ8h0AMglJOC8zuep1_bVcNvngd4CnVq6dDG-dqPd3tqQETB3LqcgG7ikYF3tcMGkwrWjM-lq6wKzO0mzSb4NtM45IhsopsGXHAA6l_rlhSfJfyrh9yKCHotN38sfknWHOVY4GAnhqeZYSHZ1IsGY9pKe7eiyIzqN5_pJiC3b1VUg4FsgH_cpXHw1ZGv_xBxLTWfQDOPUhd5kepNNoJlY8ry0IDMfBoqTo0lWs9hgOq8RMZsrGqCjkgKou-_CBeqaI7oXbEktQEDWh19ZwIrAc9JmZhyJ19GopLGY3yTaMSttJ73MGcBEWWl0rHftMIhy4mnTlojGtyM5b1_3Q7bVO0K9KxEojtZ3z7lx8-vJ_DnJ7jg_lvboQGuB_QUpiWID1xh4nQ7A1Xto7_yAomjzw3F-BGJL_AFsRYlM-qgkrUiwsrsW-16fqglsJL5wWhfY3Z-O6F1qzM0TahaoVSDKI0Zjkgs9ALd3ieO0OjvfNlD629v-J8lz4Oie2Kz8wG